        "content": "<p>How do I <code>nolint simpNF</code> the declarations generated by <code>@[simps]</code>? Just <code>@[simps, nolint simpNF]</code> doesn’t work. See <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/2198\">!4#2198</a> for an example where we have a false positive but I don’t know a way to turn off the linter. </p>\n<p>Other discussion at </p>\n<ul>\n<li><a class=\"stream-topic\" data-stream-id=\"287929\" href=\"/#narrow/stream/287929-mathlib4/topic/CategoryTheory.2EAdjunction.2EBasic\">#mathlib4 &gt; CategoryTheory.Adjunction.Basic</a> </li>\n<li><a class=\"stream-topic\" data-stream-id=\"287929\" href=\"/#narrow/stream/287929-mathlib4/topic/simps.20and.20simpNF.20linter\">#mathlib4 &gt; simps and simpNF linter</a></li>\n</ul>",
        "id": 328288242,
        "sender_full_name": "Matthew Ballard",
        "timestamp": 1676566863
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Would it make sense to register a global option for this?</p>",
        "id": 328288469,
        "sender_full_name": "Matthew Ballard",
        "timestamp": 1676566926
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You can use <code>attribute [nolint simpNF] generated_decl</code></p>",
